value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of germ cell proliferation.

label.value: negative regulation of germ cell proliferation

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of germ cell proliferation.

label.value: positive regulation of germ cell proliferation

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of germ cell proliferation.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of gonad development.
Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of gonad development.
Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of gonad development.

label.value: regulation of response to calcium ion

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of response to calcium ion.

label.value: negative regulation of response to calcium ion

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of response to calcium ion.

label.value: positive regulation of response to calcium ion

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of response to calcium ion.

label.value: negative regulation of calcium ion import across plasma membrane

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of calcium ion import across plasma membrane.

definition.value: An example of this is PPP3CA in human (Q08209) in PMID:17640527 (inferred from direct assay).

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of lipid localization.
Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of lipid localization.
Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of lipid localization.

label.value: negative regulation of endothelial tube morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of endothelial tube morphogenesis.

label.value: positive regulation of endothelial tube morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of endothelial tube morphogenesis.

label.value: regulation of cellular response to alcohol

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cellular response to alcohol.

label.value: negative regulation of cellular response to alcohol

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cellular response to alcohol.

label.value: positive regulation of cellular response to alcohol

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cellular response to alcohol.
The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized features of a glutamatergic neuron.
Any apoptotic process in a retinal cell.

label.value: compound eye retinal cell apoptotic process

value.value: Any apoptotic process in a compound eye retinal cell.

label.value: calcium ion export across plasma membrane

value.value: The directed movement of calcium ions from inside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the extracellular region.
A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a location on or within a lipid droplet.

label.value: anterograde neuronal dense core vesicle transport

value.value: The directed movement of substances in neuronal dense core vesicles along axonal microtubules towards the presynapse.

label.value: retrograde neuronal dense core vesicle transport

value.value: The directed movement of neuronal dense core vesicles along axonal microtubules towards the cell body.
Any apoptotic process in a lens fiber cell. Lens fiber cells are elongated, tightly packed cells that make up the bulk of the mature lens in a camera-type eye.
The process whereby a membrane-bounded vesicle is released into the extracellular region by fusion of the limiting endosomal membrane of a multivesicular body with the plasma membrane.
Binding to euchromatin, a dispersed and relatively uncompacted form of chromatin.

A protein complex capable of catalyzing the transfer of a group, e.g. a methyl group, glycosyl group, acyl group, phosphorus-containing, or other groups, from one compound (generally regarded as the donor) to another compound (generally regarded as the acceptor).
Binding to a steroid hormone.
Binding to a keratin filament, an intermediate filament composed of acidic and basic keratins (types I and II), typically expressed in epithelial cells.
The movement of a neutrophil within or between different tissues and organs of the body.
A process in which RNA is transported to and maintained in a part of a chromosome that is organized into chromatin.
A protein complex facilitating transport of molecules (proteins, small molecules, nucleic acids) into, out of or within a cell, or between cells.

definition.value: An example of this is GTR1 in human (UniProt symbol P11166) in PMID:15449578 (inferred from direct assay).

value.value: The reproductive developmental process whose specific outcome is the progression of the baculum over time, from its formation to the mature structure.
The directed movement of lipid molecules passing through the blood-brain barrier.
Any process that reduces or removes the toxicity of iron ion. These include transport of iron away from sensitive areas and to compartments or complexes whose purpose is sequestration of iron ion.

Steps required to transform a dense core granule generated at the trans-Golgi network into a fully formed and transmissible dense core granule. Dense core granule maturation proceeds through clathrin-mediated membrane remodeling events and is essential for efficient processing of cargo within dense core granules as well as for removing factors that might otherwise interfere with dense core granule trafficking and exocytosis.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cytoplasmic translational termination.

The multiplication or reproduction of sebocytes by cell division, resulting in the expansion of their population. A sebocyte is an epithelial cell that makes up the sebaceous glands, and secrete sebum.

The multiplication or reproduction of cholangiocytes, resulting in the expansion of the cholangiocyte population. A cholangiocyte is an epithelial cell that is part of the bile duct. Cholangiocytes contribute to bile secretion via net release of bicarbonate and water.
A process that results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a presynaptic active zone.

The multiplication or reproduction of granulosa cells, resulting in the expansion of the granulosa cells population. A granulosa cell is a supporting cell for the developing female gamete in the ovary of mammals. They develop from the coelomic epithelial cells of the gonadal ridge.

Any process carried out at the cellular level that reduces or removes the toxicity of a toxic substance. These may include transport of the toxic substance away from sensitive areas and to compartments or complexes whose purpose is sequestration of the toxic substance.

The directed movement of a Schwann cell guided by a specific chemical concentration gradient. Movement may be towards a higher concentration (positive chemotaxis) or towards a lower concentration (negative chemotaxis).

A process in which force is generated within smooth muscle tissue, resulting in a change in muscle geometry of the large intestine, exclusive of the rectum. The colon is that part of the large intestine that connects the small intestine to the rectum.
The flow of blood through the gastric mucosa of an animal, enabling the transport of nutrients and the removal of waste products.
A process in which force is generated within smooth muscle tissue, resulting in a change in muscle geometry in the intestine between the stomach and the large intestine.
A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, the cell periphery.

Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a double-stranded DNA stimulus.
